---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { ReportCard } from '../components/ReportCard';
---

<Layout title="BGP Report Card">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50">
    {/* Header */}
    <header class="bg-indigo-900 text-white shadow-md">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-6">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center">
          <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">BGP Report Card</h1>
            <p class="text-indigo-200 mt-1">Daily snapshot of global routing stability</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 md:mt-0 text-sm bg-indigo-800/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 border border-indigo-700">
            Real-time telemetry via <span class="font-semibold text-indigo-300">BGP-Stream</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      {/* RPKI Educational Section */}
      <section class="mb-10 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            🛡️ What is RPKI and Why is it Important?
          </h2>
          <div class="prose text-gray-600 space-y-4">
            <p>
              The Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) was designed without built-in security, meaning any network can accidentally or maliciously claim to own IP addresses they don't actually control. This leads to severe outages and traffic interception known as <strong>BGP Hijacking</strong> or <strong>Route Leaks</strong>.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>RPKI (Resource Public Key Infrastructure)</strong> solves this by adding cryptographic signatures to routing data. It allows network operators to verify that the Autonomous System (ASN) announcing a block of IP addresses is officially authorized to do so.
            </p>
            <p>
              The visualizations below act as a report card to show how secure BGP currently is based on ASN-to-IP validations. However, securing the internet requires ISPs and network operators to actively <em>enforce</em> RPKI filtering (Route Origin Validation) and drop invalid announcements.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <a
              href="https://isbgpsafeyet.com/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 bg-emerald-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-emerald-700 transition-colors"
            >
              Check "Is BGP Safe Yet?"
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://blog.cloudflare.com/is-bgp-safe-yet-rpki-routing-security-initiative/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-200 transition-colors"
            >
              Read Cloudflare's RPKI Initiative
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* React Dashboard Component */}
      <ReportCard client:only="react" />

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
